public class WorldEdge extends com.telenav.mesakit.graph.Edge
An edge in a WorldGraph, scoped by a WorldCell and having a WorldEdgeIdentifier. The cell for this graph element can be retrieved with worldCell() and an override of the identifier() method from Edge returns the WorldEdgeIdentifier for the edge. Other methods (from(), to(), etc) are overridden to ensure that graph elements accessed through a world edge continue to be scoped by cell.

Note that there are two methods to retrieve the graph of this GraphElement. The graph() method overrides graph() to return the WorldGraph that contains this element, while the subgraph() method returns the graph where the element is actually stored (the cell sub-graph of the world graph).

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
